Here is JavaScript code that draws firework explosions on a canvas in the shape of Bratislava:

```js
const canvas = document.getElementById("canvas");
const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

function drawBratislava() {
  ctx.beginPath();
  // Draw outline of Bratislava 
  ctx.moveTo(100, 200);
  ctx.lineTo(200, 100);
  ctx.lineTo(300, 200);
  ctx.lineTo(200, 300);
  ctx.lineTo(100, 200);
  ctx.stroke();  
}

function drawFirework() {
  const x = Math.random() * canvas.width;
  const y = Math.random() * canvas.height;
  const radius = Math.random() * 15 + 5;

  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.arc(x, y, radius, 0, Math.PI * 2);
  ctx.fillStyle = "orange";
  ctx.fill();
}

function animate() {
  ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
  drawBratislava();
  for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
    drawFirework();  
  }
  requestAnimationFrame(animate);
}

animate();
```

This code:

- Gets the canvas element 
- Draws an outline of Bratislava using lines and coordinates
- The drawFirework() function randomly places 8 orange firework explosions within the canvas 
- The animate() function clears the canvas, redraws Bratislava, then calls drawFirework() 8 times to create new fireworks
- animate() uses requestAnimationFrame to repeatedly call itself and animate the fireworks

Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.

Here is JavaScript code to draw an outline of Slovakia's borders on a canvas:

```js
const canvas = document.getElementById("canvas"); 
const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

function drawSlovakia() {
  ctx.beginPath();
  ctx.moveTo(100, 150); // Top left point
  ctx.lineTo(200, 100);  
  ctx.lineTo(300, 150);   
  ctx.lineTo(350, 200);   
  ctx.lineTo(400, 250);
  ctx.lineTo(350, 300);
  ctx.lineTo(300, 350);  
  ctx.lineTo(200, 400); 
  ctx.lineTo(100, 350);
  ctx.lineTo(50, 300);  
  ctx.lineTo(0, 250);  
  ctx.lineTo(50, 200);
  ctx.closePath();

  ctx.strokeStyle = "black";
  ctx.lineWidth = 3;
  ctx.stroke();
}

drawSlovakia();
```

This code:

- Gets the canvas element 
- Uses ctx.beginPath() to start a new path 
- Uses ctx.moveTo() and ctx.lineTo() to draw lines between coordinates that approximate Slovakia's borders
- Sets the stroke style and width  
- Calls ctx.stroke() to draw the outline of the path
- Calls the drawSlovakia() function to render the borders on load

The coordinates are approximations to generally match the shape of Slovakia. You could improve the accuracy by finding more precise coordinates for major points along the actual borders.

Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.
